definition.value: An EC 1.1.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-OH group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alcohol oxidase (EC 1.1.3.13).
An EC 4.2.1.* (hydro-lyases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cystathionine beta-synthase (EC 4.2.1.22).
An  EC 2.3.1.* (acyltransferase transferring other than amino-acyl group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of mitochondrial carnitine O-palmitoyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.21).
An N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl group in which beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc is linked beta(1->6) to the D-GalNAc group which has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre.
A carbohydrate derivative arising formally from the elimination of water from a glycosidic hydroxy group and an H atom bound to an oxygen, carbon, nitrogen or sulfur atom of a separate entity.
The L-alpha-amino acid anion that is a conjugate base of L-cystine, formed by loss of a proton from each of the carboxy groups.  It is the major microspecies at pH > 9.4.
A prosolanapyrone that is prosolanapyrone II in which the hydroxy group has been oxidised to afford the corresponding aldehyde.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from deprotonation of at least one of the acidic hydroxy groups from the phosphate moiety of a ribonucleoside monophosphate.
The leukotriene anion that is the monoanion of leukotriene D4 arising from deprotonation of the two carboxy groups and protonation of the cysteinyl alpha-amino group.

An indole alkaloid having a ajmalan-type skeleton and characterised by a 17alpha-acetoxy group, a 21beta-methyl group, loss of the 1-methyl group with associated unsaturation at N(1)=C(2), and a 20alpha-hydroxymethyl group in place of the 20beta-ethyl side-chain.

An indole alkaloid having a ajmalan-type skeleton and characterised by a 17alpha-acetoxy group, a 21beta-methyl group, loss of the 1-methyl group with associated unsaturation at N(1)=C(2), and a 20alpha-formyl group in place of the 20beta-ethyl side-chain.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a pterin ring system having a pyran ring ortho-fused at any position.
Coumarin carrying a methyl group at C-4 and a succinyl-leucyl-tryrosyl side-chain at C-7.
A nitrotoluene bearing a single nitro substituent at any position. A "closed class".
An inhibitor that interferes with the process of T-cell proliferation.
An N-hydroxysuccinimide ester derived from 4-(N-maleimidomethyl)cyclohexane-1-carboxylic acid.
A small protein-like chain designed to mimic a peptide.
A carboxylic ester obtained by formal condensation of 9-(alpha-D-galactosyloxy)nonanoic acid and methanol.
The pentacyclic triterpenoid that is the 11alpha-hydroxy derivative of beta-amyrin.
An edaxadiene in which the carbon bearing the hydroxy group has R configuration.
A  monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-alaninamide and (2Z)-2-(2-furyl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
An edaxadiene in which the carbon bearing the hydroxy group has S configuration.
A  monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-serinamide and (2Z)-2-(2-furyl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
A  monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-cysteinamide and (2Z)-2-(2-furyl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-3,3-dimethoxyalaninamide and (2Z)-2-(2-furyl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
The pentacyclic triterpenoid that is the 11-oxo derivative of beta-amyrin.
An amino acid amide that is a carboxamide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-alaninamide and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
An amino acid amide that is a carboxamide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-serinamide and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
An  amino acid amide that is a carboxamide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-cysteinamide and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-3,3-dimethoxyalaninamide and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetic acid.
An L-alanine derivative obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-alaninamide and 2-thienylacetic acid.

A beta-caryophyllene in which the stereocentre adjacent to the exocyclic double bond has R configuration while the remaining stereocentre has S configuration. It is the enantiomer of (-)-beta-caryophyllene, which occurs much more widely than the (+)-form.

A sesquiterpene with a [7.2.0]-bicyclic structure comprising fused 9- and 4-membered rings, with a trans-ring junction, a trans-double bond between the 4- and 5-positions of the 9-membered ring, a methylidene group at position 9, and methyl groups at positions 3, 11, and 11. The most commonly occurring form is the (1R,9S)-(-)-enantiomer, which is found in many essential oils, particularly clove oil.
A L-serine derivative obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-serinamide and 2-thienylacetic acid.
A cysteine derivative obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-cysteinamide and 2-thienylacetic acid.
A hexosamine having a 3-dimethylamino-3,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-galactose structure, the amino sugar constituent of ravidomycin and other antibiotics.
A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-alaninamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-phenylacetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.

A carbotricyclic compound that is tricyclo[6.3.1.0(2,5)]dodecane which is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and by methyl groups at positions 4, 4, and 8 (the  1S,2R,5S,8R-diastereoisomer).
A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-serinamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-phenylacetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.
A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-cysteinamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-phenylacetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.
A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-alaninamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.

A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-serinamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen. A synthetic determinant of cefadroxil, it is a promising tool for determining in vitro cross-reactivity to cefadroxil in amoxicillin-allergic patients.
A dipeptide consisting of N-butyl-L-cysteinamide having an (R)-2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetyl residue attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.
A dTDP-sugar having D-ravidosamine as the sugar component.
A member of the cadinene family of sesquiterpenes in which the isopropyl group is cis to the hydrogen at the adjacent bridgehead carbon (the 1R,4aS,8aS enantiomer).
An alanine derivative obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-alaninamide and (R)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetic acid.
A member of the cadinene family of sesquiterpenes in which the isopropyl group is cis to the hydrogen at the adjacent bridgehead carbon (the 1S,4aR,8aR enantiomer).
A L-serine derivative obtained by formal condensation between N-butyl-L-serinamide and (R)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetic acid.
A mycinamicin composed of a 16-membered ring macrolactone core, an N,N-dimethylated deoxysugar desosamine and a 2-O-methylated 6-deoxysugar javose.
